ACT - Variable in class aston.group20.model.Airport
 
AirControlTower - Class in aston.group20.model
The Air Control Tower class manages the queues containing the active aircraft; it ensures that the aircraft within the queues are sorted correctly based on the strategy comparator that was passed through from the Airport class.
AirControlTower(Strategy) - Constructor for class aston.group20.model.AirControlTower
Creating a new AirControlTower, which will initialise the queues and set the strategy for how to manage the Incoming aircraft.
Aircraft - Class in aston.group20.model
The Aircraft class implements the IAircraft interface and contains the fields shared by all Aircraft and the majority of the method implementation required by the IAircraft interface, however it still allows for expansion and currently has two the two separate types of Aircraft below it (Powered & Unpowered) as well as the concrete subclasses (Commercial, Glider, Light).
Aircraft(int, int) - Constructor for class aston.group20.model.Aircraft
Creating a new Aircraft which takes two parameters, the landing time and the takeoff time of the aircraft, both of which are measured in half minutes.
Airport - Class in aston.group20.model
The Airport class is used to model an Airport; it has a Runway that planes can land on/takeoff from, it has a Hangar where Aircrafts are stored(/created in this Simulation) and an Air Control Tower which holds/ does the more autonomous management of the Aircraft queues.
Airport() - Constructor for class aston.group20.model.Airport
Creating a new Airport, which will initialise the AirControlTower, Runway, and Hangar.
airport - Variable in class aston.group20.model.Simulator
